s(m) = \sum_{k=1,\ldots,m-1} \sigma(k)\,\sigma(m - k)
\begin{aligned} 	\sum_{m=1}^\infty s(m)\,q^m &= \left(\frac{1-P(q)}{24}\right)^2 \\	&= \frac{1 - 2P(q) + P^2(q)}{24^2} = 	\frac{1 - 2P(q) + Q(q) + 12q\frac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{d}q}P(q)}{24^2} \\	&= \frac{1}{12} \sum_{m=1}^\infty 	\left((1 - 6m)\,\sigma(m) + 5\sigma_3(m)\right) q^m \end{aligned}
